    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know you aren't a doctor but i'm just looking for some general info. i've read that with some meds it's actually better to take smaller amounts more often to keep the levels steady in your blood rather than waiting for the pain to hit hard. does that logic apply to ibuprofen too? like would taking 400mg every 2 hours be a more efficient way to keep the inflammation down compared to the usual way?",
